      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Mesh convergence study demonstrates that discretization error in the hemolysis index QoI is below 10% relative to the finest mesh solution.",
      "rationale": "Three-level mesh refinement study performed using meshes of 2.1M, 4.8M, and 9.6M cells. Richardson extrapolation applied to normalized index of hemolysis (NIH) values. Grid convergence index (GCI) for NIH was 4.2% on the medium mesh, satisfying the Gradation 2 threshold. Medium mesh selected for production runs."
    },
    {
      "factorStandard": "ASME-VV40-2018",
      "factorType": "Test conditions",
      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
