      "acceptanceCriteria": "Experimental test conditions used for validation are documented and sufficiently representative of the COU operating envelope, including flow rate and rotational speed ranges.",
      "rationale": "Validation experiments conducted using bovine blood at five operating points spanning 2.5–6.0 L/min and 2000–3500 RPM. Test conditions bracket the intended CPB operating range. Temperature, hematocrit, and inlet boundary conditions are documented in the experimental protocol consistent with Gradation 2."
    },
    {
