      "type": "CredibilityFactor",
      "requiredLevel": 2,
      "achievedLevel": 2,
      "factorStatus": "assessed",
      "acceptanceCriteria": "Predicted NIH values agree with experimental measurements within combined model and measurement uncertainty bounds at all five operating points.",
      "rationale": "CFD-predicted NIH values compared against experimental measurements at all five operating points. Mean absolute error of 8.3% observed; all predictions fall within combined uncertainty bands. The worst-case operating point (4.0 L/min, 3500 RPM) correctly identified by both model and experiment, satisfying the Gradation 2 output comparison requirement."
    },
