      "acceptanceCriteria": "The QoIs used in validation (NIH, relative hemolysis index RH) are directly relevant to the COU decision criterion of RH < 1 relative to predicate device.",
      "rationale": "Normalized index of hemolysis and relative hemolysis index are the primary outputs compared against the predicate device. These QoIs directly support the regulatory acceptance criterion (RH < 1). The mapping from CFD stress fields to hemolysis index via the power-law damage model is documented and clinically relevant at Gradation 2."
    },
